</Accordion>

## Embedded media

Digital Touch and handwritten messages can carry embedded media that is not a normal attachment. Fetch it with:

```ts
const media = await im.messages.getEmbeddedMedia(chat.guid, message.guid);
console.log(media.mimeType, media.data.byteLength);
```

`getEmbeddedMedia(...)` returns raw media bytes plus the detected MIME type. It throws `NotFoundError` when the chat or message cannot be resolved, and `ValidationError` with `code === ErrorCode.operationNotSupported` when the message exists but is not a supported Digital Touch or handwritten message.

## Message events

Subscribe to live message changes:

```ts
for await (const event of im.messages.subscribeEvents({ chat: chat.guid })) {
  switch (event.type) {
    case "message.received":
      console.log(event.message.guid, event.message.content.text);
      break;
    case "message.edited":
      console.log(event.messageGuid, event.editedAt);
      break;
  }
}
```

`subscribeEvents(...)` returns a `TypedEventStream<MessageEvent>`. Pass `{ chat: chat.guid }` to scope the stream to one chat; omit the filter to receive message events for all chats.

<Accordion title="MessageEvent" description="Message changes emitted by im.messages.subscribeEvents(...).">
  | `event.type` | Extra fields |
  |---|---|
  | `message.received` | `message` |
  | `message.edited` | `messageGuid`, `content`, `editedAt` |
  | `message.read` | `messageGuid`, `readAt` |
  | `message.unsent` | `messageGuid`, `retractedAt` |
  | `message.reactionAdded` | `messageGuid`, `reaction`, `targetPartIndex?` |
  | `message.reactionRemoved` | `messageGuid`, `reaction`, `targetPartIndex?` |
  | `message.stickerPlaced` | `messageGuid`, `sticker?`, `placement?`, `targetPartIndex?` |
</Accordion>

All message events include `sequence`, `chatGuid`, `isFromMe`, `occurredAt`, and optional `actor`.

Live streams are observation APIs. Use the response from a write method as the authoritative result for that write, and use [Events](/advanced-kits/imessage/events) after disconnects.
